A '''pendulum clock''' was an ancient type of [[Chronometer/Legends|chronometer]], consisting of a long weighted pendulum that swung side to side, making a distinctive ''tock'' sound every second.

One very expensive clock was kept by [[Queen Mother]] [[Tenel Ka Djo]] in her [[Queen Mother's Special Salon|Special Salon]] on [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]]. In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] came to be in its presence while they were awaiting an audience with Tenel Ka. C-3PO assumed it to be pre-[[Lorell]]ian, looted from a [[Balmorra/Legends|Balmorran]] colony ship by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]]. Han found the "tocking" to be so annoying that Leia had to restrain him from throwing a priceless [[Larmalstone|larmal]]-topped end table at it.

